  <title class="- topic/title ">Remembering Report Settings</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">When you remember report settings, your
	 report setting will be shown the next time you or anyone else in your account
	 views reports for the campaign. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
    <steps id="steps_649580383C0D41139D8D8D6A5EE4A9BF" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
      <step id="step_8519276E0F254579B918BD6B7A37C78E" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Remember Report
				Settings</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">
            <note class="- topic/note ">Changes to date range, control
				  experience and comparison column will also affect the leading experience on the
				  Campaign Home Page. 
				</note>
          </p>
          <p class="- topic/p ">Because 
				<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Remember Report
				  Settings</uicontrol> affects all users of the account, it is not available to
				read-only users.
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
